$ Oracle: Install Instant Client in Linux

The following shell commands try to demonstrate how parts of Oracle's instant can be installed on Linux. It installes the *Basic Light* package (only English error messages and US and European character set),
→ development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus and *tools* (Data Pump, → development/databases/Oracle/tools/sql-loader and Workload Replay Client).

code {
DESTDIR=~/oracle

if [ ! -e client.zip ]; then
   wget https://download.oracle.com/otn_software/linux/instantclient/2110000/instantclient-basiclite-linux.x64-21.10.0.0.0dbru.zip -O client.zip
fi

if [ ! -e sqlplus.zip ]; then
   wget https://download.oracle.com/otn_software/linux/instantclient/instantclient-sqlplus-linuxx64.zip -O sqlplus.zip
fi

if [ ! -e tools.zip ]; then
   wget https://download.oracle.com/otn_software/linux/instantclient/2110000/instantclient-tools-linux.x64-21.10.0.0.0dbru.zip -O tools.zip
fi

if [ ! -e $DESTDIR ]; then
   mkdir -p $DESTDIR
fi

→ Linux/shell/commands/unzip -o -d $DESTDIR client.zip
→ Linux/shell/commands/unzip -o -d $DESTDIR sqlplus.zip
→ Linux/shell/commands/unzip -o -d $DESTDIR tools.zip
code }

{ Setting PATH and LD_LIBRARY_PATH to execute binaries

 `LD_LIBRARY_PATH` must be set to the directory into which the files were extracted:
code {
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$DESTDIR/instantclient_21_10:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH
code }

  Then, the binaries can be executed:
code {
$DESTDIR/instantclient_21_10/sqlplus …
code }

  Adding the directory to `PATH` as well allows to execute the binaries without having to type the full path to the executable:
code {
PATH=$PATH:$DESTDIR/instantclient_21_10:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH
code }

}

links:
  Find the newest zip files in the → https://www.oracle.com/database/technologies/instant-client/linux-x86-64-downloads.html[download page].
